claim.claim-text:
2. An optical disc device recording data on an optical disc by projecting a laser beam on said optical disc such that a linear density of the data becomes substantially constant, the device comprising: 
velocity judging means for judging a recordable velocity for an optical recording medium inserted into said optical disc device; 
velocity changing means for changing a recording velocity designated from a host; 
recording velocity detecting means for detecting said recording velocity during a recording; and 
recording velocity transmitting means for transmitting information concerning said recording velocity to said host, said recording velocity being detected by said recording velocity detecting means.
